<P>The great defalcation in the nominal dollars, ari&s;es from the remittances being made in funds which &s;ell at 10 per cent. under par, and the pay|ments being made in foreign money, at a rate very much above par,&mdash;that at Leghorn in particular
<PB N="107" REF="032877_0055_0FF5A8B40C863CE0">
has advanced 16, 18 per cent. above what it was not a long time &s;ince.</P>
<P><TABLE>
<ROW>
